  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q035.a003.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">which by its very nature is contrary to charity is a mortal sin by reason of its genus. And such is sloth, because the proper effect of charity is joy in God , as stated above ( II-II:28:1 ), while sloth is sorrow about spiritual good in as much as it is a Divine good . Therefore sloth is a mortal sin in respect of</data>
