  <data key="d8">II-II q.1 — Faith</data>
  <data key="d9">question</data>
  <data key="d10">contains_article</data>
  <data key="d11">st.ii-ii.q001.a008</data>
  <data key="d12">II-II q.1 a.8 — The number of articles</data>
  <data key="d13">article</data>
  <data key="d14"></data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q001.a008.obj1</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">It would seem that the articles of faith are unsuitably formulated. For those things, which can be known by demonstration, do not belong to faith as to an object of belief for all, as stated above ( Article 5 ). Now it c</data>
  <data key="d18">structural</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q001" target="st.ii-ii.q001.a009" id="structural.st.ii-ii.q001.contains.st.ii-ii.q001.a009">
