  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">It would seem that to believe in not meritorious . For the principle of all merit is charity , as stated above ( I-II:114:4 ). Now faith , like nature , is a preamble to charity . Therefore, just as an act of nature is n</data>
