  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">Chrysostom (Hom. xli in Matth.), say that the sin against the Holy Ghost is literally to utter a blasphemy against the Holy Spirit , whether by Holy Spirit we understand the essential name applicable to the whole Trinity , each Person of which is a Spirit and is holy , or the personal name</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_structural_editorial</data>
</edge>
