  <data key="d14"></data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q015.a001.obj1</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">It would seem that blindness of mind is not a sin . Because, seemingly, that which excuses from sin is not itself a sin . Now blindness of mind excuses from sin ; for it is written ( John 9:41 ): "If you were blind, you </data>
  <data key="d18">structural</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q015" target="st.ii-ii.q015.a002" id="structural.st.ii-ii.q015.contains.st.ii-ii.q015.a002">
  <data key="d6">structural.st.ii-ii.q015.contains.st.ii-ii.q015.a002</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q015</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.15 — The vices opposed to knowledge and understanding</data>
