  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q015.a003.obj1</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">It would seem that blindness of mind and dulness of sense do not arise from sins of the flesh. For Augustine (Retract. i, 4) retracts what he had said in his Soliloquies i, 1, " God Who didst wish none but the clean to k</data>
