  <data key="d14"></data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q016.a001.obj1</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">It would seem that, in the Old Law , there should have been given precepts of faith . Because a precept is about something due and necessary . Now it is most necessary for man that he should believe , according to Hebrew</data>
  <data key="d18">structural</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q016" target="st.ii-ii.q016.a002" id="structural.st.ii-ii.q016.contains.st.ii-ii.q016.a002">
  <data key="d6">structural.st.ii-ii.q016.contains.st.ii-ii.q016.a002</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q016</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.16 — The precepts of faith, knowledge and understanding</data>
  <data key="d9">question</data>
  <data key="d10">contains_article</data>
  <data key="d11">st.ii-ii.q016.a002</data>
  <data key="d12">II-II q.16 a.2 — The precepts concerning the gifts of knowledge and understanding</data>
  <data key="d13">article</data>
  <data key="d14"></data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q016.a002.obj1</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">It would seem that the precepts referring to knowledge and understanding were unfittingly set down in the Old Law . For knowledge and understanding pertain to cognition. Now cognition precedes and directs action. Therefo</data>
  <data key="d18">structural</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q017" target="concept.eternal_life" id="edge.st.ii-ii.q017.treated_in.concept.eternal_life">
  <data key="d6">edge.st.ii-ii.q017.treated_in.concept.eternal_life</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q017</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.17 — Hope, considered in itself</data>
  <data key="d9">question</data>
  <data key="d10">treated_in</data>
  <data key="d11">concept.eternal_life</data>
  <data key="d12">Eternal Life</data>
