  <data key="d10">contains_article</data>
  <data key="d11">st.ii-ii.q021.a003</data>
  <data key="d12">II-II q.21 a.3 — To what is it opposed?</data>
  <data key="d13">article</data>
  <data key="d14"></data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q021.a003.obj1</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">It would seem that presumption is more opposed to fear than to hope. Because inordinate fear is opposed to right fear. Now presumption seems to pertain to inordinate fear, for it is written ( Wisdom 17:10 ): "A troubled </data>
