  <data key="d10">contains_article</data>
  <data key="d11">st.ii-ii.q021.a004</data>
  <data key="d12">II-II q.21 a.4 — From what vice does it arise?</data>
  <data key="d13">article</data>
  <data key="d14"></data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q021.a004.obj1</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">It would seem that presumption does not arise from vainglory. For presumption seems to rely most of all on the Divine mercy. Now mercy [misericordia] regards unhappiness [miseriam] which is contrary to glory . Therefore </data>
