  <data key="d17">y: wherefore when the Law was given these precepts were set forth from the very outset under form of a command. Yet the precepts of hope and faith were not to be given under the form of a command, since, unless man already believed and hoped, it would be useless to give him the Law : but, just a</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_structural_editorial</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q022" target="st.ii-ii.q022.a001" id="structural.st.ii-ii.q022.contains.st.ii-ii.q022.a001">
  <data key="d6">structural.st.ii-ii.q022.contains.st.ii-ii.q022.a001</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q022</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.22 — The precepts relating to hope and fear</data>
  <data key="d9">question</data>
  <data key="d10">contains_article</data>
  <data key="d11">st.ii-ii.q022.a001</data>
  <data key="d12">II-II q.22 a.1 — The precepts relating to hope</data>
