  <data key="d14"></data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q022.a002.obj1</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">It would seem that, in the Law , there should not have been given a precept of fear. For the fear of God is about things which are a preamble to the Law , since it is the "beginning of wisdom." Now things which are a pre</data>
  <data key="d18">structural</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q023" target="st.ii-ii.q023.a001" id="structural.st.ii-ii.q023.contains.st.ii-ii.q023.a001">
  <data key="d6">structural.st.ii-ii.q023.contains.st.ii-ii.q023.a001</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q023</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.23 — Charity, considered in itself</data>
