  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q023.a001.obj1</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">It would seem that charity is not friendship. For nothing is so appropriate to friendship as to dwell with one's friend, according to the Philosopher (Ethic. viii, 5). Now charity is of man towards God and the angels , "</data>
  <data key="d18">structural</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q023" target="st.ii-ii.q023.a002" id="structural.st.ii-ii.q023.contains.st.ii-ii.q023.a002">
  <data key="d6">structural.st.ii-ii.q023.contains.st.ii-ii.q023.a002</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q023</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.23 — Charity, considered in itself</data>
  <data key="d9">question</data>
  <data key="d10">contains_article</data>
  <data key="d11">st.ii-ii.q023.a002</data>
  <data key="d12">II-II q.23 a.2 — Is it something created in the soul?</data>
  <data key="d13">article</data>
  <data key="d14"></data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q023.a002.obj1</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">It would seem that charity is not something created in the soul . For Augustine says (De Trin. viii, 7): "He that loveth his neighbor, consequently, loveth love itself." Now God is love. Therefore it follows that he love</data>
  <data key="d18">structural</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q023" target="st.ii-ii.q023.a003" id="structural.st.ii-ii.q023.contains.st.ii-ii.q023.a003">
  <data key="d6">structural.st.ii-ii.q023.contains.st.ii-ii.q023.a003</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q023</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.23 — Charity, considered in itself</data>
  <data key="d9">question</data>
  <data key="d10">contains_article</data>
  <data key="d11">st.ii-ii.q023.a003</data>
  <data key="d12">II-II q.23 a.3 — Is it a virtue?</data>
  <data key="d13">article</data>
  <data key="d14"></data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q023.a003.obj1</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">It would seem that charity is not a virtue . For charity is a kind of friendship. Now philosophers do not reckon friendship a virtue , as may be gathered from Ethic. viii, 1; nor is it numbered among the virtues whether </data>
  <data key="d18">structural</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q023" target="st.ii-ii.q023.a004" id="structural.st.ii-ii.q023.contains.st.ii-ii.q023.a004">
  <data key="d6">structural.st.ii-ii.q023.contains.st.ii-ii.q023.a004</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q023</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.23 — Charity, considered in itself</data>
  <data key="d9">question</data>
  <data key="d10">contains_article</data>
  <data key="d11">st.ii-ii.q023.a004</data>
  <data key="d12">II-II q.23 a.4 — Is it a special virtue?</data>
  <data key="d13">article</data>
  <data key="d14"></data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q023.a004.obj1</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">It would seem that charity is not a special virtue . For Jerome says: "Let me briefly define all virtue as the charity whereby we love God " [The reference should be to Augustine , Ep. clxvii]: and Augustine says (De Mor</data>
  <data key="d18">structural</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q023" target="st.ii-ii.q023.a005" id="structural.st.ii-ii.q023.contains.st.ii-ii.q023.a005">
  <data key="d6">structural.st.ii-ii.q023.contains.st.ii-ii.q023.a005</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q023</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.23 — Charity, considered in itself</data>
  <data key="d9">question</data>
  <data key="d10">contains_article</data>
  <data key="d11">st.ii-ii.q023.a005</data>
  <data key="d12">II-II q.23 a.5 — Is it one virtue?</data>
  <data key="d13">article</data>
  <data key="d14"></data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q023.a005.obj1</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">It would seem that charity is not one virtue . For habits are distinct according to their objects. Now there are two objects of charity — God and our neighbor—which are infinitely distant from one another. Therefore char</data>
  <data key="d18">structural</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q023" target="st.ii-ii.q023.a006" id="structural.st.ii-ii.q023.contains.st.ii-ii.q023.a006">
  <data key="d6">structural.st.ii-ii.q023.contains.st.ii-ii.q023.a006</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q023</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.23 — Charity, considered in itself</data>
