  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q023.a007.obj1</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">It would seem that there can be true virtue without charity . For it is proper to virtue to produce a good act. Now those who have not charity , do some good actions, as when they clothe the naked, or feed the hungry and</data>
  <data key="d18">structural</data>
</edge>
