  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q024.a002.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">fore charity can be in us neither naturally , nor through acquisition by the natural powers, but by the infusion of the Holy Ghost , Who is the love of the Father and the Son, and the participation of Whom in us is created charity , as stated above ( II-II:23:2 ).</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_structural_editorial</data>
</edge>
