  <data key="d10">contains_article</data>
  <data key="d11">st.ii-ii.q024.a001</data>
  <data key="d12">II-II q.24 a.1 — Is charity in the will as its subject?</data>
  <data key="d13">article</data>
  <data key="d14"></data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q024.a001.obj1</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">It would seem that the will is not the subject of charity . For charity is a kind of love. Now, according to the Philosopher (Topic. ii, 3) love is in the concupiscible part. Therefore charity is also in the concupiscibl</data>
  <data key="d18">structural</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q024" target="st.ii-ii.q024.a002" id="structural.st.ii-ii.q024.contains.st.ii-ii.q024.a002">
  <data key="d6">structural.st.ii-ii.q024.contains.st.ii-ii.q024.a002</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q024</data>
