  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q024.a002.obj1</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">It would seem that charity is not caused in us by infusion. For that which is common to all creatures, is in man naturally . Now, according to Dionysius (Div. Nom. iv), the "Divine good ", which is the object of charity </data>
  <data key="d18">structural</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q024" target="st.ii-ii.q024.a003" id="structural.st.ii-ii.q024.contains.st.ii-ii.q024.a003">
  <data key="d6">structural.st.ii-ii.q024.contains.st.ii-ii.q024.a003</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q024</data>
