  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q026.a006.obj1</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">It would seem that we ought not to love one neighbor more than another. For Augustine says (De Doctr. Christ. i, 28): "One ought to love all men equally. Since, however, one cannot do good to all, we ought to consider th</data>
  <data key="d18">structural</data>
</edge>
