  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q026.a013.obj1</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">It would seem that the order of charity does not endure in heaven . For Augustine says (De Vera Relig. xlviii): "Perfect charity consists in loving greater goods more, and lesser goods less." Now charity will be perfect </data>
  <data key="d18">structural</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q027" target="concept.charity" id="edge.st.ii-ii.q027.treated_in.concept.charity">
