  <data key="d14">ann.st-ii-ii-q028-treated-in-concept-joy-st-ii-ii-q028-a001-resp</data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q028.a001.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">As stated above ( I-II:25:1 , I-II:25:2 , I-II:25:3 ), when we were treating of the passions , joy and sorrow proceed from love, but in contrary ways. For joy is caused by love, either through the presence of the thing loved, or because the proper good of th</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_structural_editorial</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q028" target="st.ii-ii.q028.a001" id="structural.st.ii-ii.q028.contains.st.ii-ii.q028.a001">
  <data key="d6">structural.st.ii-ii.q028.contains.st.ii-ii.q028.a001</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q028</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.28 — Joy</data>
  <data key="d9">question</data>
  <data key="d10">contains_article</data>
  <data key="d11">st.ii-ii.q028.a001</data>
  <data key="d12">II-II q.28 a.1 — Is joy an effect of charity?</data>
  <data key="d13">article</data>
  <data key="d14"></data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q028.a001.obj1</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">It would seem that joy is not effected in us by charity . For the absence of what we love causes sorrow rather than joy . But God , Whom we love by charity , is absent from us, so long as we are in this state of life, si</data>
  <data key="d18">structural</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q028" target="st.ii-ii.q028.a002" id="structural.st.ii-ii.q028.contains.st.ii-ii.q028.a002">
  <data key="d6">structural.st.ii-ii.q028.contains.st.ii-ii.q028.a002</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q028</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.28 — Joy</data>
  <data key="d9">question</data>
  <data key="d10">contains_article</data>
  <data key="d11">st.ii-ii.q028.a002</data>
  <data key="d12">II-II q.28 a.2 — Is this kind of joy compatible with sorrow?</data>
  <data key="d13">article</data>
  <data key="d14"></data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q028.a002.obj1</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">It would seem that the spiritual joy that results from charity is compatible with an admixture of sorrow. For it belongs to charity to rejoice in our neighbor's good , according to 1 Corinthians 13:4-6 : " Charity . . . </data>
  <data key="d18">structural</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q028" target="st.ii-ii.q028.a003" id="structural.st.ii-ii.q028.contains.st.ii-ii.q028.a003">
  <data key="d6">structural.st.ii-ii.q028.contains.st.ii-ii.q028.a003</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q028</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.28 — Joy</data>
  <data key="d9">question</data>
  <data key="d10">contains_article</data>
  <data key="d11">st.ii-ii.q028.a003</data>
  <data key="d12">II-II q.28 a.3 — Can this joy be full?</data>
  <data key="d13">article</data>
  <data key="d14"></data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q028.a003.obj1</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">It would seem that the spiritual joy which proceeds from charity cannot be filled. For the more we rejoice in God , the more is our joy in Him filled. But we can never rejoice in Him as much as it is meet that we should </data>
  <data key="d18">structural</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q028" target="st.ii-ii.q028.a004" id="structural.st.ii-ii.q028.contains.st.ii-ii.q028.a004">
  <data key="d6">structural.st.ii-ii.q028.contains.st.ii-ii.q028.a004</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q028</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.28 — Joy</data>
  <data key="d9">question</data>
  <data key="d10">contains_article</data>
  <data key="d11">st.ii-ii.q028.a004</data>
  <data key="d12">II-II q.28 a.4 — Is it a virtue?</data>
  <data key="d13">article</data>
  <data key="d14"></data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q028.a004.obj1</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">It would seem that joy is a virtue . For vice is contrary to virtue . Now sorrow is set down as a vice , as in the case of sloth and envy . Therefore joy also should be accounted a virtue .</data>
  <data key="d18">structural</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q029" target="concept.charity" id="edge.st.ii-ii.q029.treated_in.concept.charity">
  <data key="d6">edge.st.ii-ii.q029.treated_in.concept.charity</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q029</data>
