  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q029.a003.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">Peace implies a twofold union, as stated above ( Article 1 ). The first is the result of one's own appetites being directed to one object; while the other results fr</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_structural_editorial</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q029" target="st.ii-ii.q029.a001" id="structural.st.ii-ii.q029.contains.st.ii-ii.q029.a001">
  <data key="d6">structural.st.ii-ii.q029.contains.st.ii-ii.q029.a001</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q029</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.29 — Peace</data>
  <data key="d9">question</data>
  <data key="d10">contains_article</data>
  <data key="d11">st.ii-ii.q029.a001</data>
  <data key="d12">II-II q.29 a.1 — Is peace the same as concord?</data>
  <data key="d13">article</data>
  <data key="d14"></data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q029.a001.obj1</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">It would seem that peace is the same as concord. For Augustine says (De Civ. Dei xix, 13): "Peace among men is well ordered concord." Now we are speaking here of no other peace than that of men . Therefore peace is the s</data>
  <data key="d18">structural</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q029" target="st.ii-ii.q029.a002" id="structural.st.ii-ii.q029.contains.st.ii-ii.q029.a002">
  <data key="d6">structural.st.ii-ii.q029.contains.st.ii-ii.q029.a002</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q029</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.29 — Peace</data>
  <data key="d9">question</data>
  <data key="d10">contains_article</data>
  <data key="d11">st.ii-ii.q029.a002</data>
  <data key="d12">II-II q.29 a.2 — Do all things desire peace?</data>
  <data key="d13">article</data>
  <data key="d14"></data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q029.a002.obj1</data>
  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">It would seem that not all things desire peace. For, according to Dionysius (Div. Nom. xi), peace "unites consent." But there cannot be unity of consent in things which are devoid of knowledge . Therefore such things can</data>
  <data key="d18">structural</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q029" target="st.ii-ii.q029.a003" id="structural.st.ii-ii.q029.contains.st.ii-ii.q029.a003">
  <data key="d6">structural.st.ii-ii.q029.contains.st.ii-ii.q029.a003</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q029</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.29 — Peace</data>
  <data key="d9">question</data>
  <data key="d10">contains_article</data>
  <data key="d11">st.ii-ii.q029.a003</data>
  <data key="d12">II-II q.29 a.3 — Is peace an effect of charity?</data>
