  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q041.a001.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">While contention implies a contradiction of words, strife denotes a certain contradiction of deeds . Wherefore a gloss on Galatians 5:20 says that "strifes are when persons strike one another through anger ." Hence st</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_structural_editorial</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q041" target="concept.war" id="edge.st.ii-ii.q041.treated_in.concept.war">
  <data key="d6">edge.st.ii-ii.q041.treated_in.concept.war</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q041</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.41 — Strife</data>
