  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q041.a001.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">alatians 5:20 says that "strifes are when persons strike one another through anger ." Hence strife is a kind of private war , because it takes place between private persons , being declared not by public authority, but rather by an inordinate will. Therefore strife is always sinful</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_structural_editorial</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q041" target="st.ii-ii.q041.a001" id="structural.st.ii-ii.q041.contains.st.ii-ii.q041.a001">
