  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">As stated above ( II-II:16:1 ; I-II:99:1 ), a precept implies the notion of something due. Hence a thing is a matter of precept, in so far as it is something due. Now a thing is due in two ways, for its own sake, and for the sake of something else. On every af</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_structural_editorial</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q044" target="st.ii-ii.q044.a001" id="structural.st.ii-ii.q044.contains.st.ii-ii.q044.a001">
