<edge source="st.ii-ii.q001.a008" target="concept.article_of_faith" id="edge.st.ii-ii.q001.a008.treated_in.concept.article_of_faith">
  <data key="d6">edge.st.ii-ii.q001.a008.treated_in.concept.article_of_faith</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q001.a008</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.1 a.8 — The number of articles</data>
  <data key="d9">article</data>
  <data key="d10">treated_in</data>
  <data key="d11">concept.article_of_faith</data>
  <data key="d12">Article of Faith</data>
  <data key="d13">doctrine</data>
  <data key="d14">ann.st-ii-ii-q001-a008-treated-in-concept-article-of-faith-st-ii-ii-q001-a008-resp</data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q001.a008.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">As stated above (Articles 4 and 6 ), to faith those things in themselves belong, the sight of which we shall enjoy in eternal life , and by which we are brought to eternal life . Now two things are proposed to us to be seen in eternal life : viz. the secret of</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_structural_editorial</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q001.a008" target="concept.faith" id="edge.st.ii-ii.q001.a008.treated_in.concept.faith">
  <data key="d6">edge.st.ii-ii.q001.a008.treated_in.concept.faith</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q001.a008</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.1 a.8 — The number of articles</data>
  <data key="d9">article</data>
  <data key="d10">treated_in</data>
  <data key="d11">concept.faith</data>
  <data key="d12">Faith</data>
  <data key="d13">virtue</data>
  <data key="d14">ann.st-ii-ii-q001-a008-treated-in-concept-faith-st-ii-ii-q001-a008-resp</data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q001.a008.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">As stated above (Articles 4 and 6 ), to faith those things in themselves belong, the sight of which we shall enjoy in eternal life , and by which we are brought to eternal life</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_structural_editorial</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q001.a009" target="concept.faith" id="edge.st.ii-ii.q001.a009.treated_in.concept.faith">
  <data key="d6">edge.st.ii-ii.q001.a009.treated_in.concept.faith</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q001.a009</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.1 a.9 — The manner of embodying the articles in a symbol</data>
  <data key="d9">article</data>
  <data key="d10">treated_in</data>
  <data key="d11">concept.faith</data>
  <data key="d12">Faith</data>
  <data key="d13">virtue</data>
  <data key="d14">ann.st-ii-ii-q001-a009-treated-in-concept-faith-st-ii-ii-q001-a009-resp</data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q001.a009.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">Hence the need for the truth of faith to be collected together, so that it might the more easily be proposed to all, lest anyone might stray from the truth through ignorance of the faith</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_structural_editorial</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q001.a009" target="concept.symbol_of_faith" id="edge.st.ii-ii.q001.a009.treated_in.concept.symbol_of_faith">
  <data key="d6">edge.st.ii-ii.q001.a009.treated_in.concept.symbol_of_faith</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q001.a009</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.1 a.9 — The manner of embodying the articles in a symbol</data>
  <data key="d9">article</data>
  <data key="d10">treated_in</data>
  <data key="d11">concept.symbol_of_faith</data>
  <data key="d12">Symbol of Faith</data>
  <data key="d13">doctrine</data>
  <data key="d14">ann.st-ii-ii-q001-a009-treated-in-concept-symbol-of-faith-st-ii-ii-q001-a009-resp</data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q001.a009.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">It is from its being a collection of maxims of faith that the symbol [The Greek symballein ] takes its name.</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_structural_editorial</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q001.a010" target="concept.faith" id="edge.st.ii-ii.q001.a010.treated_in.concept.faith">
  <data key="d6">edge.st.ii-ii.q001.a010.treated_in.concept.faith</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q001.a010</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.1 a.10 — Who has the right to propose a symbol of faith?</data>
  <data key="d9">article</data>
  <data key="d10">treated_in</data>
  <data key="d11">concept.faith</data>
  <data key="d12">Faith</data>
  <data key="d13">virtue</data>
  <data key="d14">ann.st-ii-ii-q001-a010-treated-in-concept-faith-st-ii-ii-q001-a010-resp</data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q001.a010.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">Consequently to publish a new edition of the symbol belongs to that authority which is empowered to decide matters of faith finally, so that they may be held by all with unshaken faith</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_structural_editorial</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q001.a010" target="concept.symbol_of_faith" id="edge.st.ii-ii.q001.a010.treated_in.concept.symbol_of_faith">
